\title{ Approach to the semiconductor cavity QED in
high-Q regimes with q-deformed boson}
\maketitle
\thispagestyle{empty}
\vspace{15mm}
\begin{abstract}
The high density Frenkel exciton which interacts with a single mode microcavity 
field is dealed with in the framework of the q-deformed boson. It is shown that the q-defomation
of bosonic commutation relations is satisfied naturally by the exciton operators when
the low density limit is deviated. An analytical expression of the 
physical spectrum for the exciton is given by using of the dressed states of 
the cavity field and the exciton. We also give the numerical study and compare
the  theoretical results with the experimental results
\end{abstract}
